This article is a press release from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, dated May 10, 2012. It announces an executive order signed by President Barack Obama titled "Identifying and Reducing Regulatory Burdens." The order aims to modernize the regulatory system and reduce unjustified regulatory burdens and costs. It emphasizes the importance of agencies conducting retrospective analyses of existing rules to determine if they remain justified and should be modified or streamlined. The executive order also encourages public participation in retrospective review and sets priorities for agencies to focus on initiatives that produce significant monetary savings or reductions in paperwork burdens while protecting public health, welfare, safety, and the environment. Agencies are required to regularly report on their retrospective review efforts to the Office of Information and Regulatory Affairs. The order includes general provisions and clarifies that it does not impair existing authorities or create any new rights or benefits enforceable by any party against the United States.